answer:
The project fine-tunes the embedding model instead of just using the base sentence-transformer because it improves retrieval over the base model. This is stated in the ROADMAP.md file.

In more detail, the README.md file explains that the LLM chooses tools (search/read/list/grep) in a loop when the --agent tool-loop flag is used. The --finetuned flag can be set to "true" to search using the fine-tuned embedding model instead of the base model. This allows for better retrieval metrics like MRR, nDCG and Recall.

